Subject: [PATCH] p2p: qualify Network() return type to fix GCC C++20 error

GCC (C++20 mode) treats a method named `Network()` returning an
unqualified `Network*` as a "changes meaning" error, because the method
name shadows the class name `Network` inside its own declaration.
Qualify the return type with `::webrtc::` to disambiguate.

diff --git a/p2p/base/port_interface.h b/p2p/base/port_interface.h
--- a/p2p/base/port_interface.h
+++ b/p2p/base/port_interface.h
@@ -52,7 +52,7 @@ class PortInterface {
   virtual ~PortInterface();
 
   virtual IceCandidateType Type() const = 0;
-  virtual const Network* Network() const = 0;
+  virtual const ::webrtc::Network* Network() const = 0;
 
   // Methods to set/get ICE role and tiebreaker values.
   virtual void SetIceRole(IceRole role) = 0;
